quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  44,1,"Ha Mīm."
  44,2,"By the Evident Scripture,"
  44,3,"We have indeed sent it down on a blessed night{1}. Indeed, We have always been warning.",footnotes:1:This night is known as the night of <i>Qadr </i>(Surah number 97), in the month of Ramadan.
  44,4,"Onit, every wise command is distinguished—"
  44,5,"a command from Us; indeed, We have always been sending"
  44,6,"mercy from yoursg Lord—indeed, it is He who is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing—"
  44,7,"<i class=""s"">(from the) </i><span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Asem, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…the All-Knowing. <sub lang="en-GB"><small>7</small></sub>7 (He is the) Lord of the…”</span>
  44,8,"There is no god but He; He gives life and causes death—yourpl Lord and the Lord of your ancient fathers."
  44,9,"Yet they play around in doubt."
  44,10,"So waitsg and watch out for the day when the sky produces evident smoke"